### Get Non-existent Connection (Expected 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/management/connections/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-Organization-Id: {{organizationId}}

###

### Get Non-existent Job (Expected 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/fetcher/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-Organization-Id: {{organizationId}}

### =============================================================================
### SSL CONNECTION EXAMPLES
### =============================================================================

### Create PostgreSQL Connection with SSL
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/management/connections
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-Organization-Id: {{organizationId}}
X-Product-Name: reporter

{
    "configName": "postgres_ssl",
    "type": "POSTGRESQL",
    "host": "secure-db.example.com",
    "port": 5432,
    "databaseName": "production",
    "userName": "dbuser",
    "password": "secretpassword",
    "ssl": {
        "mode": "require"
    }
}

###

### Create PostgreSQL Connection with SSL Certificates
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/management/connections
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-Organization-Id: {{organizationId}}
X-Product-Name: reporter

{
    "configName": "postgres_ssl_certs",
    "type": "POSTGRESQL",
    "host": "secure-db.example.com",
    "port": 5432,
    "databaseName": "production",
    "userName": "dbuser",
    "password": "secretpassword",
    "ssl": {
        "mode": "verify-full",
        "ca": "-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----\n...\n-----END CERTIFICATE-----",
        "cert": "-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----\n...\n-----END CERTIFICATE-----",
        "key": "-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\n...\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----"
    }
}

### =============================================================================
### COMPLETE WORKFLOW EXAMPLE
### =============================================================================
### Execute these requests in order to test a complete flow:
### 1. Create a connection (associated with a product via header)
### 2. Test the connection
### 3. Get the connection schema
### 4. Validate the schema
### 5. Create a fetcher job
### 6. Get job status (poll until completed)
### =============================================================================

### Step 1: Create PostgreSQL Connection for Workflow
# @name workflowCreateConnection
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/management/connections
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-Organization-Id: {{organizationId}}
X-Product-Name: reporter

{
    "configName": "workflow_postgres",
    "type": "POSTGRESQL",
    "host": "localhost",
    "port": 5432,
    "databaseName": "external_transactions",
    "userName": "postgres",
    "password": "postgres"
}

###

### Step 2: Test Connection
# @name workflowTestConnection
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/management/connections/{{workflowCreateConnection.response.body.id}}/test
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-Organization-Id: {{organizationId}}

###

### Step 3: Get Connection Schema
# @name workflowGetSchema
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/management/connections/{{workflowCreateConnection.response.body.id}}/schema
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-Organization-Id: {{organizationId}}

###

### Step 4: Validate Schema
# @name workflowValidateSchema
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/management/connections/validate-schema
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-Organization-Id: {{organizationId}}

{
    "mappedFields": {
        "workflow_postgres": {
            "transactions": ["id", "account_id", "amount", "currency", "status", "created_at"]
        }
    }
}

###

### Step 5: Create Fetcher Job
# @name workflowCreateJob
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/fetcher
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-Organization-Id: {{organizationId}}

{
    "dataRequest": {
        "mappedFields": {
            "workflow_postgres": {
                "transactions": ["id", "account_id", "amount", "currency", "status", "created_at"]
            }
        }
    },
    "metadata": {
        "source": "workflow_test",
        "workflow": "complete_flow"
    }
}

###

### Step 6: Get Job Status (poll until status is "completed" or "failed")
# @name workflowGetJobStatus
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/fetcher/{{workflowCreateJob.response.body.jobId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-Organization-Id: {{organizationId}}

###

### Cleanup: Delete Connection
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/v1/management/connections/{{workflowCreateConnection.response.body.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-Organization-Id: {{organizationId}}
